@NODE "Prefs"

  akJFIFPrefs
  -----------
  akJFIFPrefs is the Preferences Program for akJFIF.datatype.

  GUI has been designed with StormWizard 2.0, so this program needs
  "wizard.library" V42+ (you can find a copy on Aminet under
  "biz/haage/WizardLibrary.lha" or even never versions under
  ftp.haage-partner.com).

  Icon by Bert Bosma <lmb@wxs.nl> (based on NewIcons).

  Task (process) specific settings also can be done - either using
  the preferences program (which allows to select the corresponding
  process from a list as long as it actually is running at the same
  time) or by hand, following the scheme below:

                           OPTIONAL
  ---------------- task specific settings files -----------------------
  Settings specific to different caller programs may be created
  by copying the global settings from "Datatypes/akJFIF.prefs" to an
  optional task-related prefs file called

            "Datatypes/akJFIF.prefs_Tasks/TaSkNaMe"

  where "TaSkNaMe" means the name of the program as e.g. shown by
  a system monitor (for obvious reasons, this does work best with
  workbench programs, which don't require name patterns as some
  CLI programs might do, like for example "CLI(3):Work:Browsers/XWebber").
  So, with AWeb for example, you would just edit your global settings
  file and then do the following:

    MakeDir ENV:Datatypes/akJFIF.prefs_Tasks
    Copy ENV:Datatypes/akJFIF.prefs ENV:Datatypes/akJFIF.prefs_Tasks/AWebIP"

     [... and the same for ENVARC: ...]

  After that, AWeb will ignore the global settings and fetch its own
  from the given file.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  Public options (available via prefs program):

   DECODE_METHOD=
        <FAST_INTEGER|
         SLOW_INTEGER>          => see prefs program
   COLOR_QUANTIZING=<FAST|SLOW> => see prefs program
   UPSAMPLING=<ON|OFF>          => see prefs program
   SCALE_DENOM=<0..3>           => see prefs program

  Hidden options (not available via prefs program):

   CUSTOM_MODES=<0x...hexID...> => use a fixed viewmode always
   NOASPECT                     => use fixed 1:1 aspect always
                                   (no calculation, faster)
   THRESH_WIDTH                 => see below
   THRESH_HEIGHT                => see below
   DEBUG                        => enable debug mode (output)

  THRESH_WIDTH & THRESH_HEIGHT prefs options are for finegraining
  the SCALE_DENOM behaviour; if an image has a width or height smaller
  than one of those thresh values, the selected scaling factor is
  not applied; instead the factor is incremented by 1 binary step
  (e.g. 1/4 instead of 1/8) and if all tried factors still would
  result in an image size smaller than the tresh values no scaling
  would be done at all - this makes it much easier to pre-configure
  and utilize akJFIF for thumbnail generation because usually for a
  thumbnail size of 96x96 you only want to scale down images sized
  e.g 102x768 by 1/8 but not those which would end up being much smaller
  than the available thumbnail area - for these first try 1/4,
  then 1/2 then 1/1...

  WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS version does not support
           alpha channel handling, then always set STRIPALPHA=ON
           (no ARGB/RGBA)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

 History
 =======
 V45.95 (30.12.2008):  - removed MOS support, as there are more
                         frequent MOS updates now and as there still
                         is no fully featured new SDK for external 
                         developers; makes semi-redundant datatype
                         development finally quite pointless
                       - copyright bump

 V45.92 (13.9.2008):   - added missing descriptor .info file
                       - removed some legacy library opening code
                       - MOS 1.4.5 no longer supported;
                         now testing using MOS 2.0 (2.1)

 V45.91 (18.3.2008):   - synchronized builds

 V45.89 (2.2.2008):    - bumped

 V45.88 (20.1.2008):   - bumped

 V45.87 (7.1.2008):    - fixed version/date strings for V45.86
                       - fixed the viewmode fix from V45.86
                         a second time

 V45.86 (5.1.2008):    - fixed long-standing MOS bug in viewmode
                         generation routine (did not occur with 68k
                         and did only pop up with some graphics)

 V45.85 (4.1.2008):    - MOS/68k: now really building from same
                                  source tree; the following
                                  information is relative to
                                  the former MOS tree
                       - improved MOS startup code
                       - fixed possible bug source in one prefs
                         setting handler
                       - added DEBUG switch (i.e. now disabled
                         by default)
                       - documented all prefs settings again
                         in the @{"Prefs" LINK Prefs} section
                       - Prefs: made the labels easier to understand,
                                especially the alpha settings

 V45.84 (2.1.2008):    - Copyright bump to 2008
                       - MOS: added some 68k optimizations also here
                       - some additions to asyncio routines
                       - improvements in asyncio routines
                       - minor optimization in dispatcher
                       - MOS: 68k was already using V43 in 8 bit
                              mode (only for grayscaled images)
                              but MOS did not yet

 V45.83 (28.12.2007): - fixed bug in asyncio dispatcher, which
                        could have lead to a stale file lock,
                        thus memory loss, in case of DOS fallback
                        during AsyncIO availability

 V45.81 (18.11.2007): - now properly supports CMYK, YCCK
                        and YCbCr conversion to RGB

 V45.79 (5.10.2007):  - now that V40 dithering is gone, the
                        corresponding code in libjpeg is, too

                        68k: ca.  8k saved per .datatype
                        MOS: ca. 15k saved

                      - MOS: disabled SAS/C specific libjpeg
                             optimization for GCC, finally

 V45.78 (2.10.2007):  - Prefs: - added "Reset" option for
                                 default settings

                      - MOS:   - was still parsing pre-V45.70
                                 settings, which could have led
                                 to problems with fresh setups
                               - removed 24 bit -> 8 bit dithering
                               - removed 24 bit -> HAM 6/8 conversion
                               - 8 bit settings could have led to
                                 instable behaviour previously;
                                 now these settings are no longer
                                 available

                      - enhanced async/normal IO dispatcher

                      - documented THRESH_ options

 V45.70 (1.8.2007):   - 68k: removed all V40 legacy code
                      - 68k: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                      - 68k: removed 24 bit -> 8 bit dithering
                      - 68k: removed 24 bit -> HAM 6/8 conversion
                      - 68k: removed all V40-related settings

                      - memory-related optimizations

                      - Prefs: removed all V40-related settings
                      - Prefs: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                      - Prefs: will not run with wizard-lib < V42 anymore

 V45.66 (27.7.2007):  - updated german .guide file

 V45.65 (15.7.2007):  - added THRESH_WIDTH. THRESH_HEIGHT prefs
                        options for finegraining the SCALING
                        behaviour; if an image has a width or
                        height smaller than one of those thresh
                        values, the selected scaling factor is
                        not applied; instead the factor is incremented
                        by 1 binary step (e.g. 1/4 instead of 1/8)
                        and if all tried factors still would result
                        in an image size smaller than the tresh
                        values no scaling would be done at all
                      - this makes it much easier to pre-configure
                        and utilize akJFIF for thumbnail generation
                        because usually for a thumbnail size of
                        96x96 you only want to scale down images
                        sized e.g 102x768 by 1/8 but not those
                        which would end up being much smaller than
                        the available thumbnail area - for these
                        first try 1/4, then 1/2 then 1/1...

                      - MOS version was still V45.63 (no changes)

                      - address change

 V45.64 (7.6.2007):   - 68k versions were broken due to exotic
                        math library linker issue, resulting in
                        strange effects, like "out of memory"
                        (-> Thomas Klein)

 V45.63 (3.6.2007):   - reduced size of all 68k versions by ca. 9kb
                      - optimized error handling
                      - killed some (partially dead) references
                        to standard C library
                      - removed floating point support
                      - fixed MOS build problem
                      - optimized prefs parsing under MOS, too
                      - at some - less important - point, the
                        prefs program was mixing up fast and
                        slow IDCT (oops) - i.e. slow as default

 V45.62 (25.5.2007):  - memory allocation routine now adapts itself
                        better to system config (pool adjustment)
                      - optimized pool configuration in general

 V45.60 (29.4.2007):  - prefs program now creates env "tasks" dir
                        prior to saving task-specific prefs
                        (-> Bernd Roesch)

 V45.56 (13.1.2007):  - MOS dt version ID still was 45.50 (updated)
                      - do not set interleaved flag when allocating
                        bitmaps of depth 1 (which should never happen)
                      - MOS: disabled HAM 6/8 in prefs program and removed
                        all related code from datatype since it crashes
                        MorphOS under Pegasos (there is 24 bit anyway,
                        so we use this as fallback now - also on the GUI)

 V45.55 (26.11.2006): - upaded installer
                      - minor fixes in .guide

 V45.51 (11.7.2006):  - improved 2 descriptors & 2 new added

 V45.50 (15.5.2006):  - removed V44 dither option
                        (should be set by calling application instead)

 V45.49 (19.3.2006):  - minor changes in the codec

 V45.46 (18.2.2006):  - deleted german Datatypes FAQ due to bad translation
                        (sorry that I did not recognize this earlier)
                        and obsolete information
                      - in general cleaned up documentation
                      - cleaned up same areas in english guide file
                      - prepared for OM_GET and DTA_Methods

 V45.30 (16.1.2006):  - small corrections
                      - now DONATION WARE (see www.ar-kleinert.de)

 V45.28 (24.5.2005):  - further MOS specific optimizations
                      - improved version checks (OS 3.1)
                      - MOS prefs program has certain options disabled

 V45.27 (16.5.2005):  - code cleanup

 V45.26 (14.5.2005):  - Installer fix
                      - optimization++

 V45.25 (13.5.2005):  - integrated MorphOS version
                      - improved error handling

 V45.8  (29.10.2002): - bugfix of V45.5

 V45.5  (25.10.2002): - increased memory consumption for better speed,
                        fallback to slower code when memory is low (V43, 24 bit only)

 V45.1   (29.6.2002): - added further 68k and Amithlon/UAE optimizations

 V44.140 (28.6.2002): - removed PPC support; added Amithlon/UAE optimizations

 V44.131 (15.12.2001):- Prefs program and docs updated

 V44.122 (21.8.2001): - speedup (changed behaviour on unreg. version)

 V44.121 (21.8.2001): - speedup

 V44.120 (21.8.2001): - history cleaned up

